<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-02-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-02-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="212" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d212">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 184/111</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Administrative Officer of the
                            Commission to Negotiate Peace</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Patterson</hi>)</head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-02-19">February 19, 1919</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p rend="flushleft">Memorandum No. 79</p>
                    <p rend="flushleft">Subject: Division of Current Diplomatic and Political
                        Correspondence.</p>
                    <p>1. A new section of the Secretariat, the Division of Current Diplomatic and
                        Political Correspondence, has been established, room 415 <pb facs="0546" n="510" xml:id="pg_510"/> Hotel Crillon, telephone Crillon 41, Mr. Ellis
                        L. Dresel in charge. The symbol for his office, to be used in the
                        distribution of documents, is S–D.</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">R. C. Patterson, Jr</hi>.</signed><lb/><hi rend="italic">Captain, U. S. A.</hi></closer>
                    <postscript>
                        <p>Approved:<lb/><hi rend="smallcaps">J. C. Grew</hi><lb/><hi rend="italic">Secretary</hi></p>
                    </postscript>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>